node.title: Three die in road crashes in Waikato
node.description: Three people have been killed in crashes in the Waikato district today, two at Eureka and one in Waitoa.
node.content:
["Three people have been killed in crashes in the Waikato district today, two at Eureka and one in Waitoa.", "", "
\nPhoto: Supplied / St John Ambulance\n
", "Three others were injured in the three-vehicle crash in Eureka, one seriously and two moderately.", "Emergency services were called to the scene just before 2pm.", "State Highway 26 between Hamilton and Morrinsville remains closed at the intersection with Hinton Rd.", "Diversions are in place at SH26 and Platt Road and SH26 and Hunter Road.", "Police also confirmed one person died following a crash in Waitoa earlier today.", "Police said the car and a truck were involved in the crash which occurred about 4:10pm on Waihekau Road.", "The road remains closed near the intersection of Seddon Road and Chudleigh Road.", "Police urge motorists to avoid the area if possible."]
